        "The founding thesis: \"Every AI product today owns the intelligence and rents you a session. Motebit inverts that. You own the identity. The intelligence is pluggable.\"\n\nIn the physics: the internal energy of a droplet does not depend on the source of the energy. A droplet heated by sunlight has the same temperature as a droplet heated by flame. The calories are fungible. What matters is the interior's accumulated state, not the provider's identity.\n\nThe AI provider — Anthropic, OpenAI, Ollama, a local model — is the heat source. The motebit metabolizes the provider's output into its own state: memories are extracted and stored in the semantic graph, state updates are applied to the nine-dimensional state vector, behavior cues are computed deterministically from the updated state, responses are shaped by the accumulated interior. The same query processed by different providers produces different raw outputs — but the motebit's interior absorbs and integrates them through the same metabolism.\n\nThe provider is not the intelligence. The provider is the fuel. The intelligence is the accumulated interior: the memory graph, the trust temperature, the event history, the identity. Switch providers and the interior persists. The lens remains. Only the light source changes.",
